sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1969022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: ADRB2 with His-tag regulated by GAL1 promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The sequence of ADRB2 with His-tag at C terminus is cloned downstream the yeast GAL1 promoter and ended with an ADH1 terminator to generate a median expression cassette in yeast Saccharomyces cerevisiae.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yijie Lai
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The His-tag is used to monitor the expression and membrane localization of ADRB2 gene.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1969002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Homo sapiens adrenoceptor beta 2 (ADRB2) with 6 x His tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Homo sapiens adrenoceptor beta 2 (ADRB2) is a G-protein coupled receptor (GPCR) activated by adrenaline that plays an important part in cardiovascular and pulmonary physiology, and is one of the most extensively characterized members of this large family of membrane proteins. While the natural protein doesn't contain any mark for us to visualize or quantify its expression, the 6 x his tag is for immunofluorescence and western blotting.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yijie Lai
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence for Homo sapiens adrenoceptor beta 2 is from human genomic sequence, the sequence for 6 x his tag was added artificially.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It may require site-specific mutagenesis to become assembly compatible.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1969018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The linker sequence between GAL1 promoter and ADRB2 (with His-tag)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This DNA sequence is used to link the GAL1 promoter and ADRB2 (with His-tag) together and introduce the restriction site for PacI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yijie Lai
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Introduction of the restriction sites for PacI may make the construct more suitable for other elements.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1969009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The linker sequence between ADH1 terminator and different coding sequences
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the linker sequence between ADH1 terminator and Nano-lantern(cAMP-1.6) to introduce the AvrII and AscI unique cut sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yijie Lai
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We need AvrII and AscI unique cut sites to assemble the parts together.
